## Who Is This Deal Best For?

**If you are a pre-revenue startup,** AWS Activate is one of the highest-leverage things you can claim right now. Every dollar of runway counts, and $5,000 in credits keeps your infrastructure free for months while you iterate toward product-market fit. Apply immediately — don't wait until you're actively spending on AWS.

**If you have just raised a seed round,** you're about to start scaling your infrastructure as you bring on new users and hire engineers. AWS Activate gives you a meaningful buffer during the period when your cloud spend starts climbing but your revenue hasn't caught up yet. Use the Business Support to get architecture reviews before you build systems that are expensive to refactor later.

**If you are scaling past 10 employees,** your AWS bill is growing quickly. Even if you've been on AWS for a while, check whether you've exhausted your original Activate credits — if you have, you may be eligible for additional credits through an accelerator partner or AWS ISV program. The Business Support tier becomes increasingly valuable as your infrastructure complexity grows.

## Real Use Cases

**TalentQueue, an HR tech startup from Berlin**, used their AWS Activate credits to build and deploy a candidate matching algorithm on SageMaker. Their CTO estimated the credits saved them from having to raise an additional $15,000 to cover ML infrastructure costs in the first year. They reached 200 paying customers before spending a single dollar on AWS.

**Stackly, a B2B SaaS company**, used EC2 and RDS credits to run their entire backend infrastructure for 8 months at no cost. When they finally burned through the credits, they had enough recurring revenue to absorb the AWS bill without touching investor capital. The founder called it "the best single deal we ever claimed."

**Floro, a two-person product studio**, used S3 and Lambda credits to build a media processing pipeline for their video editing SaaS. The serverless architecture meant their AWS bill was literally $0 in months with low usage, and the credits stretched across their entire first year of operation.

## Tips to Maximize This Deal

1. **Apply before you start building** — Credits activate at application approval, not when you first use them. Apply on day one so you don't spend real money while waiting for approval.
2. **Use Reserved Instances for predictable workloads** — Once you identify services you'll run consistently, switch to Reserved Instances. This can cut costs by 30–40%, making your $5,000 stretch much further.
3. **Set a billing alert at $4,500** — You don't want to hit zero credits unexpectedly. Set a CloudWatch billing alarm so you have time to optimize or prepare for paid usage.
4. **Take advantage of AWS Business Support immediately** — Schedule an architecture review in your first month. Getting expert input early prevents expensive refactoring later.
5. **Stack with the AWS free tier** — Many AWS services have permanent free tiers (Lambda: 1M requests/month, S3: 5GB storage). Use those first so your credits go further on paid usage.
