## Who Is This Deal Best For?

**If you are a pre-revenue startup,** Notion is one of the first tools you should set up. Before you have processes, you need a place to build them. Use the free 3 months to create your company wiki, document your product decisions, build a simple roadmap, and set up a hiring tracker — everything in one place that new team members can access on day one.

**If you have just raised a seed round,** you're about to grow your team and need a knowledge base that scales. Notion's Plus plan gives you the guest access and unlimited uploads needed to onboard investors, share board materials, and collaborate with contractors. The 3 free months give you time to build a solid workspace before you're paying for multiple seats.

**If you are scaling past 10 employees,** you may want to evaluate the Business plan for more advanced permissions. But starting with the free Plus deal and migrating upward is a smart approach — you only pay for the features you actually use once the trial ends.

## Real Use Cases

**Buildfire, a 3-person SaaS startup**, used Notion to replace both Trello and Google Docs during their first 3 months. They built their product roadmap, engineering specs, sales CRM, and investor update template all inside one Notion workspace. Their first seed investor told them the organized Notion wiki was a signal that the team operated with unusual discipline for an early-stage company.

**Meridian Labs, a solo founder building a B2B tool**, used Notion's database feature to manage her entire outbound sales process. She tracked leads, conversations, and follow-up dates in a Notion database with a Kanban view. The 3-month free trial saved her from paying for a standalone CRM while she was still validating whether the product had demand.

**Quickframe, a remote team of 4 across 3 time zones**, used Notion as their async communication hub. Every project had a dedicated page with context, decisions, and status updates. New hires could get up to speed in a day by reading the relevant pages. The unlimited guest access let them share deliverable pages directly with clients instead of creating separate documents.

## Tips to Maximize This Deal

1. **Set up your company wiki on day one** — Don't wait until you have 10 people to start documenting. The best time to build a knowledge base is when the company is small and every decision is fresh.
2. **Use the 100 guest slots aggressively** — Invite advisors, investors, and contractors as guests so they have access to the context they need without you having to send constant updates.
3. **Migrate before the trial ends** — If you decide to stay on Plus after 3 months, set up billing 1 week before expiry so there's no disruption. If you're downgrading to free, review what you'll lose before you get cut off.
4. **Use templates to move fast** — Notion has hundreds of community templates for product specs, OKRs, hiring pipelines, and more. Don't build from scratch — find a template and customize it.
