## What Is Deel?

Deel is the global HR and payroll platform built for teams that hire across borders. If you want to bring on an engineer in Poland, a designer in Brazil, and a customer success manager in the Philippines — all without setting up legal entities in each country — Deel makes that possible.

Founded in 2019, Deel has grown to serve over 20,000 companies ranging from two-person startups to public companies with thousands of employees. The platform handles **contractor management**, **full-time employment via Employer of Record (EOR)**, **global payroll**, compliance documentation, and even equity management for international team members.

Before platforms like Deel existed, hiring internationally meant either paying expensive law firms to set up local entities, misclassifying employees as contractors (illegal in many countries), or simply not hiring the best person for the job because the paperwork was too hard. In 2026, that friction is gone. Deel compresses weeks of legal work into a 15-minute onboarding flow.

## Why This Deal Matters for Startups

For startups in their first year, global hiring is often the difference between a mediocre team and a great one. The best engineers, designers, and operators are distributed across the world — limiting yourself to one city or country limits the quality of your team.

**$1,500 in Deel credits** covers a meaningful chunk of the platform fees associated with your first few international hires. Deel charges a monthly fee per worker — typically $49/month for contractors and $599/month for EOR employees. Your credits can cover:

- **30 months** of contractor management for one person
- **2.5 months** of full EOR employment for one person
- A mix of contractor management across your entire early team

The deeper value is in **avoiding expensive mistakes**. Misclassifying a worker as an independent contractor when they should be a full-time employee under local law can result in fines, back taxes, and legal exposure. Deel's compliance layer prevents those mistakes — and that protection is worth far more than $1,500 in avoided penalties.

In **2026**, remote-first hiring is the standard for competitive startups. Companies that embrace global hiring have access to a 10x larger talent pool at the same budget. The $1,500 in credits removes the financial friction from making your first international hire.

## What's Included in the Deal

- **$1,500 in Deel credits** applicable to contractor management, EOR services, and payroll fees
- **Free setup and onboarding** — Deel's team will guide you through your first hire
- **Access to 150+ countries** for contractor payments and EOR employment
- **Compliance documentation** automatically generated for each country
- **Deel's contractor agreement templates** — legally vetted for each jurisdiction
- **Multi-currency payment** — pay workers in their local currency from your USD account
- Deel equity management tools for startups issuing options to international employees

**What is NOT included:**
- Credits do not cover the cost of employer taxes or social contributions in EOR countries (those are charged at cost)
- Credits expire — check the terms for the expiry window
- The deal requires a minimum 3-month commitment to the platform

## Eligibility Requirements

- Must be an **active Deel customer** or sign up through SaaSOffers as a new customer
- **Minimum 3-month commitment** required — Deel is not a one-time-use tool
