7. Start using Deel to manage global payroll and save $1,500 on platform fees in 2026

## Deel Key Features for Startups

### Employer of Record (EOR) — Hire Without a Local Entity
EOR means Deel legally employs your worker on your behalf in their country, handling all local compliance, taxes, and benefits. You manage the work, Deel handles the legal structure. This lets a US-based startup employ someone in Germany without setting up a German GmbH — a process that would normally take 3–6 months and cost $10,000+ in legal fees.

### Contractor Management — Clean, Compliant Agreements
Deel generates locally compliant contractor agreements in minutes, handles signature collection, and manages monthly invoice approvals. For startups working with freelancers across multiple countries, this eliminates the risk of using generic contractor agreements that don't hold up under local law.

### Multi-Currency Global Payroll
Your team gets paid in their local currency on a consistent schedule, while you manage everything from a single USD (or EUR) account. Deel handles the forex conversion and transfer. For a startup with team members in 5+ countries, this alone saves hours of manual wire transfers every month.

### Compliance Monitoring
Deel monitors misclassification risk for every worker and flags when a contractor relationship is starting to look like de facto employment under local law. Getting that alert proactively — rather than from a government audit — is the kind of protection that can save a startup from an existential legal bill.

### Equity Management for International Teams
International employees often can't receive standard US stock options. Deel's equity module helps structure compliant equity arrangements for team members in countries with specific restrictions, making it possible to offer competitive equity packages to your best international hires.

