## What Is Figma?

Figma is the collaborative design platform that has become the standard tool for product teams at companies of every size — from two-person startups to 10,000-person enterprises. It's where designers create interfaces, product managers annotate wireframes, and engineers inspect designs and extract production-ready CSS and assets.

What separates Figma from every tool that came before it is that it runs entirely in the browser with real-time multiplayer collaboration. No more "who has the latest version of the Sketch file" — everyone on your team works in the same file simultaneously, like Google Docs for design. This shift to browser-based, collaborative design is why Figma captured over 70% of the professional design tool market and why Adobe tried to acquire it for $20 billion in 2022.

In 2026, using Figma is table stakes for any startup building a digital product. Investors, potential hires, and enterprise customers will ask to see your designs — and they'll expect them to be in Figma.

## Why This Deal Matters for Startups

Six months of Figma Professional free is worth $450 for a small team — but the strategic value is higher. The first 6 months of a startup's product development cycle are when design decisions get made that are expensive to reverse later. Having the full Professional plan during this critical window means you're not cutting corners on your design process when it matters most.

Figma Professional removes the free plan's biggest limitations: multiple editors, unlimited version history, and advanced sharing controls. On the free tier, only 2 editors can work in a file simultaneously. For a founding team of 3 where multiple people need to edit designs, that constraint is immediately painful.

