## What Is Brex?

Brex is the corporate card and financial platform built from the ground up for startups. Unlike traditional business credit cards that require a personal guarantee — meaning your personal credit is on the line for company expenses — Brex evaluates your company's financial health directly. No personal guarantee, no personal credit check.

Founded in 2017 by former Stripe employees, Brex quickly became the default corporate card for YC-backed companies and VC-funded startups across the US. Today, over 30,000 businesses use Brex to manage spending, earn rewards on SaaS and travel purchases, and access a suite of financial tools including expense management, bill pay, and business banking.

In 2026, Brex is more than a credit card — it's a financial operating system for startups. The platform includes corporate cards (physical and virtual), a business bank account, expense reporting, bill pay automation, and a perks catalog with startup deals from AWS, Stripe, and 50+ other partners. For a founder who wants to stop using a personal credit card for company expenses, Brex is the cleanest, fastest transition.

