Every time a founder uses a personal credit card for company expenses, they're creating personal financial liability for business spending. If the company struggles, personal credit scores take the hit. Beyond the financial risk, mixing personal and company expenses creates accounting headaches, complicates tax filings, and gives investors a messy picture of company financials.

**Getting Brex from day one** means clean separation of personal and business finances, a corporate card that the whole team can use (with individual virtual cards and spend limits), and automatic expense categorization that makes month-end accounting dramatically faster.

