Mixpanel's funnel analysis lets you define any sequence of steps — sign up, complete profile, create first project, invite teammate — and see exactly what percentage of users make it through each stage. When your funnel shows 70% of users drop off between "create account" and "create first project," you know exactly where to focus product improvement. Without funnels, you're guessing at bottlenecks.

### Retention Charts — Understand Your Churn Drivers
Retention charts show you how many users from a given signup cohort are still active on day 1, day 7, day 14, and day 30. More importantly, you can segment retention by user properties — users who completed the onboarding checklist, users who invited a teammate, users who came from a specific acquisition channel. These segments reveal which early behaviors predict long-term retention, letting you engineer your onboarding around the actions that matter most.

