The Flows analysis shows you the most common paths users take through your product — both forward (what do users do after completing onboarding?) and backward (what did users who churned do in their last session?). In 2026, understanding user intent through behavioral data is more predictive than any survey or user interview. Flows surfaces patterns you wouldn't think to look for.

### Cohort Analysis — Segment Your Users by Behavior
Mixpanel lets you define user cohorts based on behavior ("users who used feature X at least 3 times in their first week") and then analyze those cohorts across any metric — retention, revenue, feature adoption. For a startup iterating on product-market fit, cohort analysis reveals which user profiles your product actually resonates with — often different from the profile you originally designed for.

