## What Is Loom?

Loom is an async video messaging platform that lets you record your screen, camera, or both and instantly share a link — no uploading, no waiting, no scheduling required. The person you share it with watches on their own time, leaves timestamped comments, and responds with their own Loom if needed. The whole exchange happens faster than scheduling a meeting and richer than a written message.

Used by over 25 million people at companies like HubSpot, Atlassian, Figma, and thousands of distributed teams worldwide, Loom has become the defining tool of async-first work culture in 2026. The product solves a real problem: most workplace communication either loses context (text messages, Slack) or requires synchronous coordination (meetings). Loom sits in the middle — high context, zero scheduling friction.

For a startup team that's distributed, remote, or simply trying to move faster than daily standups allow, Loom compresses communication cycles and frees up calendar time that would otherwise be consumed by meetings that didn't need to happen synchronously.

## Why This Deal Matters for Startups

Six months of Loom Business free is worth **$900** — but the productivity math is more compelling than the dollar savings. The average meeting costs roughly $200 in combined hourly salary for the participants. If Loom eliminates even 3 meetings per week for a 5-person team, that's $600 in recovered productivity time per week, or **$15,600 over 6 months**.

The specific Loom Business features that justify the upgrade from the free tier are: unlimited video length, engagement analytics (who watched your video and when), custom CTAs inside videos, and Loom AI (automatic transcripts, summaries, and action item extraction). These features are what separate a simple screen recorder from a professional async communication platform.

**In 2026**, remote and hybrid work is the baseline for most startups. Teams are distributed across cities or countries, working across time zones, and increasingly resistant to meetings that could have been async. Loom is the infrastructure that makes distributed teams function at the speed of co-located teams.

## What's Included in the Deal

