## Loom Key Features for Startups

### Async Video That Replaces Meetings
The most impactful use of Loom is simple: instead of scheduling a 30-minute meeting, record a 5-minute Loom. The recipient watches when it fits their schedule, rewinds the parts they need to review again, and responds asynchronously. For a 5-person remote team, eliminating 3 meetings per week through Loom recovers 15 person-hours of calendar time — every single week.

### Loom AI — Transcripts and Action Items Automatically
Every Loom recording automatically generates a transcript, an AI summary, and a list of action items. This means your team doesn't have to take notes during a Loom, and searching for what was said in a Loom from 3 months ago takes seconds. In 2026, AI-generated meeting artifacts are table stakes for knowledge work — Loom delivers this for async video without additional tools.

### Engagement Analytics — Know What Was Actually Watched
Loom Business shows you who opened your shared video, how much of it they watched, and which parts they replayed. This is invaluable for sales and customer success: if you send a product demo Loom and see that a prospect rewatched the pricing section 3 times, you know exactly what to follow up on. For internal communication, engagement analytics show whether your async updates are actually being consumed.

### Sales Outreach — Personalized Video at Scale
Personalized video outreach has dramatically higher reply rates than text-based cold email. Recording a 60-second Loom that mentions the prospect by name, references something specific about their company, and walks through how your product solves their specific problem is one of the highest-leverage things a founder can do for early sales. Loom makes recording, personalizing, and sharing these videos a 2-minute process.

