Instead of writing a 20-step onboarding guide, record a Loom walkthrough of your product's core features. Customers can watch it on demand, rewind when they get confused, and refer back to it whenever they need a refresher. For a startup doing high-touch customer onboarding with a small team, a library of Loom walkthroughs replaces hours of repetitive screen-sharing sessions.

