## Ahrefs Key Features for Startups

### Site Audit — Fix Technical Issues Hurting Your Rankings
Ahrefs' Site Audit crawls every page on your website and flags technical issues across 100+ checks. Broken internal links, pages missing meta descriptions, slow load times, duplicate content, missing alt text on images, and Core Web Vitals failures all show up in a prioritized list with explanations and fix guidance. For a startup whose website was built quickly without SEO in mind, the first audit often reveals 20–50 fixable issues that are suppressing your rankings.

### Backlink Monitoring — Know Who Links to You
Every time a new website links to yours, AWT notifies you. Every time you lose a backlink, AWT tracks it. For a startup doing content marketing, press outreach, or partnership development, this monitoring tells you which efforts are working (which outreach campaigns earned links) and which need adjustment (which link opportunities have gone cold). Backlinks remain the most important off-page ranking factor in 2026.

### Organic Keyword Tracking — Measure Your SEO Progress
AWT shows you every keyword your website currently ranks for in Google, your average position, and your position history over time. This makes SEO progress measurable — instead of "we're doing content marketing," you can say "we moved from position 23 to position 8 for our target keyword in 3 months." For investor updates and team OKRs, data-backed SEO progress is a credible, trackable metric.

### Google Search Console Integration — Deeper Click Data
Connecting AWT to your Google Search Console gives you keyword-level click data alongside Ahrefs' crawl data. You can see not just which keywords you rank for, but which keywords are actually generating clicks and impressions. This combination identifies quick win opportunities: keywords where you rank in positions 11–20 with significant impression volume, where a small ranking improvement would generate meaningful traffic.

### Core Web Vitals Monitoring
Google uses Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS) as ranking factors. AWT tracks your Core Web Vitals scores across your key pages and flags pages that are underperforming. For a startup that has shipped features quickly without optimizing performance, fixing Core Web Vitals issues is often one of the highest-ROI technical improvements available.

